===Etymology===

From Proto-Athabascan *''-ɢa̓·ŋ-əʔ''. Cognates: Western Apache ''-gan'', Chiricahua ''-gan'', Jicarilla ''-gan'', Lipan ''-gąą’'', Plains Apache ''-gąą'', Central Tanana ''-gonaʔ'', Dene Sųłiné ''-gànɛ́'', Hupa ''-ɢan-'', Rogue River ''´gʷaanɛ'', Galice ''gaaneʔ'', Eyak ''-ɢəla’''

===Noun===
'''-gaan''' (''[[inalienable]]'', e.g., '''shigaan''' "my arm", '''bigaan''' "her/his/their arm")

#[[arm]]

